cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional network for video-based physiological measurement, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions applications in human-computer interaction, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as another likely category. The use of attention mechanisms and skin reflection models indicates a focus on multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. The paper also mentions outperforming state-of-the-art methods, which suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves physiological measurement, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category.
